region's%20airports%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20close%20due%20to%20cracks%20in%20the%20runway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20search%20and%20rescue%20of%20those%20impacted%20by%20the%20quake%20is%20a%20battle%20against%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%20said%20during%20an%20emergency%20disaster%20meeting%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKishida%20said%20rescuers%20were%20finding%20it%20very%20difficult%20to%20reach%20the%20northern%20tip%20of%20the%20Noto%20peninsula%20due%20to%20wrecked%20roads%2C%20and%20that%20helicopter%20surveys%20had%20discovered%20many%20fires%20and%20widespread%20damage%20to%20buildings%20and%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20local%20authorities%2C%20Kyodo%20news%20agency%20reported%20more%20than%2020%20deaths%20from%20the%20quake.%20Public%20broadcaster%20NHK%20said%2015%20had%20died%20just%20in%20the%20hard-hit%20town%20of%20Wajima%20near%20the%20epicentre%2C%20where%20there%20were%20also%2014%20cases%20of%20people%20trapped%20in%20collapsed%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan's%20disaster%20management%20agency%20said%20it%20had%20received%20unconfirmed%20reports%20of%2019%20deaths%20earlier%20on%20Tuesday%20but%20official%20updates%20on%20the%20toll%20have%20been%20infrequent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20140%20tremors%20have%20been%20detected%20since%20the%20quake%20first%20hit%20on%20Monday%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Japan%20Meteorological%20Agency.%20The%20agency%20has%20warned%20more%20strong%20shocks%20could%20hit%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWrecked%20Homes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENobuko%20Sugimori%2C%20a%2074-year-old%20resident%20of%20Nanao%20city%20in%20Ishikawa%2C%20told%20Reuters%20she%20had%20never%20experienced%20such%20a%20quake%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20tried%20to%20hold%20the%20TV%20set%20to%20keep%20it%20from%20toppling%20over%2C%20but%20I%20could%20not%20even%20keep%20myself%20from%20swaying%20violently%20