s%20Valley%20region%20and%20had%20been%20active%20for%20more%20than%2020%2C000%20years%2C%20who%2C%20according%20to%20their%20interpretation%2C%20became%20the%20progenitor%20of%20the%20culture%20across%20the%20world%20by%20extending%20westward.%20This%20%E2%80%98out-of-India%E2%80%99%20theory%20propagated%20in%20the%20calendar%20flies%20in%20the%20face%20of%20all%20the%20available%20evidence%20generated%20by%20a%20spectrum%20of%20scientific%20and%20sociological%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F695927572%2FIIT-Kharagpur-2024-calendar%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20IIT%20Kharagpur%202024%20calendar%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EIIT%20Kharagpur%202024%20calendar%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fuser%2F286754081%2FThe-Wire%23from_embed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22View%20The%20Wire's%20profile%20on%20Scribd%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Scribd%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fembeds%2F695927572%2Fcontent%3Fstart_page%3D1%26view_mode%3Dscroll%26access_key%3Dkey-3UsUIO63ALUzXuXayL6F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20data-auto-height%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20data-aspect-ratio%3D%5C%220.45436207766011094%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22IIT%20Kharagpur%202024%20calendar%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20calendric%20narrative%20violates%20the%20evidence%20generated%20from%20archaeo-genetics%2C%20archaeology%2C%20linguistics%2C%20zoology%2C%20botany%2C%20geography%2C%20and%20theology.%20Peer-reviewed%20studies%20suggest%20that%20the%20pre-Indian%20state%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20beginnings%20are%20associated%20with%20the%20Harappans%2C%20the%20earliest%20settlers%20belonging%20to%20a%20greater%20Indus%20Valley%20civilisation%2C%20whose%20culture%20extends%20from%207%2C000%20to%202%2C000%20BCE.%20Some%20of%20them%20were%20originally%20from%20the%20Iranian%20plains%20as%20evidenced%20by%20the%20genetic%20studies%20and%20others%20could%20be%20the%20original%20inhabitants%20with%20genetic%20connections%20with%20much%20earlier%20migrants%20from%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20an%20excerpt%20in%20the%202024%20IIT%20Calendar%20from%20Swami%20Vivekananda%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EProblem%20of%20India%20and%20its%20Evolution%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0mentions%20that%20the%20Vedic%20Aryans%20reached%20from%20elsewhere%2C%20which%20goes%20against%20the%20messaging%20of%20the%20calendar%20makers%20themselves.%20But%20it%20is%20a%20retribution%20of%20sorts%20that%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20own%20words%20quoted%20from%20his%20book%20imply%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98out%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20supposition%20is%20quite%20far-fetched%20and%20grossly%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwamy%E2%80%99s%20quoted%20statement%20reads%20like%20this%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20Aryans%20reached%20India%2C%20they%20found%20the%20climate%20so%20hot%20that%20they%20could%20not%20work%20incessantly%2C%20so%20they%20began%20to%20think%3B%20thus%2C%20they%20became%20introspective%20and%20developed%20religion.%E2%80%9D%20He%20is%20further%20quoted%20as%20%E2%80%9CAnother%20branch%20of%20Aryans%20went%20into%20the%20smaller%20and%20more%20picturesque%20country%20of%20Greece%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D.%20Swami%20Vivekananda%20made%20this%20insightful%20statement%20when%20the%20knowledge%20about%20the%20Vedic%20Aryans%20was%20sketchy.%20The%20archaeological%20excavation%20in%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20started%20only%20in%201925%2C%20led%20by%20John%20Marshall%20and%20his%20Indian%20associates%2C%20marking%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20scientific%20understanding%20of%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20Indus%20settlers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpread%20around%20the%20Indus%20River%2C%20Kutch%2C%20Saurashtra%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20Baluchistan%20and%20the%20Makran%C2%A0Coast%2C%20the%20original%20settlers%20in%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20engaged%20in%20agriculture%20and%20trade%2C%20designing%20well-laid-out%20townships%20with%20a%20good%20water%20management%20system.%20Centred%20on%20farming%2C%20they%20were%20also%20good%20at%20seagoing%20and%20transacting%20goods%20with%20the%20parallelly%20flourishing%20distant%20ancient%20settlements%20like%20Mesopotamia%20and%20Egypt%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20All%20these%20communities%20including%20the%20Harappan%20society%20slowly%20declined%20because%20of%20increasing%20aridity%20and%20declining%20rainfall%20which%20became%20critical%20around%204000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scientific%20evidence%20collected%20later%20also%20suggests%20that%20during%20the%20late%20Harappan%20period%2C%20about%204000%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Rigvedic%20people%20entered%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20through%20present-day%20Iran%20and%20Afghanistan.%20These%20pastoral%20migrants%20and%20their%20grazing%20animals%20including%20horses%20came%20in%20from%20the%20Caspian%20steppes%20into%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20region%2C%20in%20batches%2C%20to%20mingle%20with%20the%20earlier%20dark-skinned%20settlers%20of%20the%20Indus%20Valley.%C2%A0Weaving%20linguistics%20and%20history%20together%2C%20Peggy%20Mohan%20in%20her%20recent%20book%2C%20%E2%80%98Wanderers%2C%20Kings%2C%20Merchants%E2%80%99%20shows%20how%20these%20emigrants%20from%20the%20Eurasian%20plains%2C%20consisting%20only%20of%20males%20mingled%20with%20the%20original%20inhabitants%20and%20married%20the%20women%20in%20those%20indigenous%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20explains%20how%20this%20interaction%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20gain%20retroflex%20sounds%20from%20the%20archaic%20Dravidian%20language%20of%20the%20original%20settlers%20in%20the%20entire%20sound%20system%20of%20Sanskrit%2C%20the%20language%20of%20the%20Vedic%20emigrants.%20She%20compares%20this%20with%20an%20analogous%20scenario%20of%20the%20emigration%20of%20the%20patrilineal%20Namboothiri%20Brahmins%20of%20North%20India%20to%20Kerala%20in%20the%20Middle%20Ages%20and%20how%20the%20interaction%20infused%20Sanskrit%20words%20in%20Malayalam%2C%20the%20local%20language.%20A%20similar%20transformation%20must%20have%20happened%20to%20the%20archaic%20Sanskrit%20when%20it%20met%20with%20the%20local%20language%20spoken%20by%20the%20Harappans%20when%20it%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20by%20the%20Vedic%20Aryans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20glaringly%20missing%20in%20the%20calendar%20is%20the%20inputs%20from%20the%20genetic%20studies%20expected%20of%20a%20product%20of%20an%20IIT%20%E2%80%93%20a%20highly%20rated%20academic%20institute%20in%20India.%20The%20recently%20conducted%20genetic%20studies%20have%20provided%20a%20solid%20justification%20for%20the%20theory%20of%20Aryan%20migration%20from%20the%20Eurasian%20steppes%20to%20India.%20These%20studies%20resulted%20in%20a%20revolutionary%20understanding%20of%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20Aryan%20nomads%20who%20reached%20the%20Indus%20Valley.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20mitochondrial%20DNA%20(haplogroup%20R1a1a)%20of%20some%20of%20the%20Brahmanical%20groups%20in%20India%20still%20share%20a%20common%20genetic%20ancestral%20lineage%20with%20Eastern%20Europeans.%20The%20batches%20of%20nomads%2C%20mostly%20males%2C%20who%20shared%20the%20genomic%20material%20must%20have%20moved%20east%20out%20of%20the%20Caspian%20grasslands%2C%20who%20were%20adept%20at%20taming%20horses%20and%20mastered%20building%20horse-drawn%20chariots%2C%20essential%20for%20a%20nomadic%20life.%20Around%201%2C900%20BCE%2C%20about%204000%20years%20ago%2C%20these%20people%20broke%20up%20and%20one%20group%20proceeded%20towards%20what%20is%20now%20Iran%2C%20and%20the%20other%20to%20India%2C%20as%20also%20implied%20by%20Swami%20Vivekananda%2C%20as%20referred%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20entered%20India%2C%20around%201%2C500%20BCE%20(about%203500%20years%20ago)%2C%20established%20the%20dominant%20civilisation%20in%20the%20north-west.%20By%20then%2C%20many%20of%20the%20older%20Harappan%20settlers%E2%80%99%20colonies%20must%20have%20been%20fragmented%20and%20they%20had%20become%20marginalised.%20The%20newly%20settled%20people%2C%20the%20so-called%20Aryans%2C%20who%20were%20worshippers%20of%20fire%20likely%20to%20have%20been%20better%20at%20conducting%20rituals%20and%20more%20creative%20intellectually.%20In%20another%20study%2C%20the%20DNA%20separated%20from%20the%20skeleton%20of%20a%20woman%20from%20a%205%2C000-year-old%20in%20the%20village%20of%20Rakhigarhi%2C%20in%20the%20Hisar%20District%20of%20Haryana%2C%20the%20lineage%20shows%20no%20detectable%20ancestry%20from%20the%20Caspian%20steppe%20pastoralists%20or%20Anatolian%20or%20Iranian%20farmers%2C%20suggesting%20initial%20farming%20in%20South%20Asia%20may%20have%20arose%20indigenously%20rather%20than%20necessarily%20from%20large-scale%20migration%20from%20the%20west.%20These%20oldest%20settlers%20may%20have%20more%20genetic%20commonality%20with%20much%20earlier%20migrants%20from%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20defenders%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98out-of-India%E2%80%99%20hypothesis%2C%20in%20their%20enthusiasm%2C%20even%20remarked%20in%20one%20part%20of%20their%20commentary%20in%20the%20calendar%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20geological%20continuity%20between%20the%20Pallakad%20(Sic)%20Gap%20in%20India%20and%20Ranotsara%20Gap%20in%20Madagascar%20is%20now%20fully%20substantiated%20evidence.%20The%20evidence%20hints%20at%20possible%20demographic%20migratory%20linkages%20between%20Africa%20and%20India%20from%20pre-history%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20a%20breathtaking%20statement.%20What%20they%20are%20referring%20to%20is%20the%20Gondwana%20Supercontinent%20that%20existed%20450%20million%20years%20ago%20when%20Africa%2C%20India%2C%20South%20America%2C%20and%20Australia%20were%20part%20of%20one%20super-continental%20mass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20ancient%20supercontinent%20broke%20up%20about%20180%20million%20years%20ago%20into%20landmasses%20we%20recognize%20today%3A%20Africa%2C%20South%20America%2C%20Australia%2C%20Antarctica%2C%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20and%20the%20Arabian%20Peninsula.%20How%20could%20the%20connectivity%20between%20the%20Palakkad%20Gap%20in%20southern%20India%20and%20the%20Ranotsara%20Gap%20in%20Madagascar%20in%20a%20geologically%20remote%20period%20offer%20a%20migratory%20path%20for%20humans%20%E2%80%93%20a%20time%20when%20even%20mammals%20were%20absent%2C%20not%20to%20speak%20of%20humans%3F%20The%20Homo%20sapiens%E2%80%94began%20their%20migration%20out%20of%20Africa%20some%2060%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20not%20billions%20of%20years%20as%20the%20calendar%20makers%20propose.%20The%20goof-up%20does%20not%20end%20there%20and%20the%20calendar%20goes%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20calling%20the%20Paleolithic%20hominid%20communities%20as%20%E2%80%98civilization%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20at%20a%20time%20when%20humans%20subsisted%20by%20hunting%20and%20scavenging%20wild%20animals%20using%20stone%20tools.%C2%A0%20India%20hosts%20several%20archaeological%20sites%20from%20where%20evidence%20of%20Palaeolithic%20communities%20dated%20to%20several%20millions%20of%20years%20has%20been%20obtained%2C%20particularly%20from%20the%20Narmada%20Valley%20in%20central%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%E2%80%99s%20IIT%20calendar%20also%2C%20like%20previous%20attempts%2C%20repeats%20the%20hoax%20that%20the%20unicorn%2C%20an%20iconic%20Indus%20Valley%20seal%2C%20belongs%20to%20the%20Vedic%20period.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20text%20that%20accompanies%20an%20image%20of%20a%20unicorn%20in%20the%202024%20calendar%20claims%C2%A0that%20the%20seal%20depicts%20a%20%E2%80%9C9-square%20or%20Navagraha%20Vedic%20Mandala%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93representing%20the%20arrangement%20of%20nine%20planets!%20I%20can%20only%20quote%20Meera%20Nanda%20in%20an%20earlier%20article%20who%20discussed%20in%20detail%20this%20unicorn%20obsession%20of%20modern%20seekers%20of%20the%20cradle%20of%20civilization%2C%20%E2%80%9CWith%20an%20undisciplined%20mythic%20imagination%2C%20combined%20with%20a%20commitment%20to%20making%20India%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccradle%20of%20civilisation%2C%E2%80%9D%20there%20is%20no%20end%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98evidence%E2%80%99%20that%20can%20be%20invented%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20for%20a%20moment%20forget%20about%20the%20questionable%20interpretation%20of%20the%20ancestry%20part%2C%20but%20I%20want%20the%20readers%20to%20go%20to%20March%20in%20this%20calendar%20of%202024%20that%20is%20available%20on%20the%20internet%20and%20see%20for%20themselves%20the%20map%20of%20India%20published%20by%20the%20calendar%20makers%20and%20compare%20it%20with%20the%20political%20map%20issued%20by%20the%20Survey%20of%20India.%20The%20map%20published%20in%20the%20calendar%20shows%20that%20the%20parts%20of%20Jammu-Kashmir%20fall%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20of%20the%20border%20shared%20by%20Pakistan.%20A%20mundane%20point%2C%20but%20it%20tells%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20slapdash%20style%20of%20the%20makers%20of%20this%20calendar%20and%20the%20sources%20they%20used%20in%20formulating%20a%20dubious%20narrative%20of%20Indian%20ancestry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IIT%20Kharagpur%20on%20their%20website%20now%20disowns%20this%20calendar.%20The%20institution%2C%20however%2C%20is%20now%20running%20a%20ticker%20on%20its%20website%20saying%20it%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20calendar.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20IKS%20Calendar%20of%202024%20(India%20of%20the%20Ages)%2C%20purported%20to%20be%20published%20by%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Kharagpur%2C%20presently%20under%20circulation%20in%20social%20media%2C%20is%20NOT%20an%20officially%20published%20calendar%20of%20IIT%20Kharagpur.%20Accordingly%2C%20the%20institute%2C%20or%20any%20of%20its%20authorities%2C%20owe%20no%20responsibility%20whatsoever%20for%20the%20veracity%20of%20its%20contents%20or%20any%20other%20issues%20arising%20from%20that%20place.%20The%20institute%20bears%20No%20Knowledge%20of%20the%20content%20that%20is%20represented%20in%20an%20individual%20capacity%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20serious%20issue%20but%20they%20do%20not%20disclose%20why%20they%20are%20disowning%20it.%20Are%20they%20disowning%20it%20because%20it%20contains%20disinformation%20and%20misinformation%20on%20Indian%20ancestry%3F%20If%20that%20is%20the%20case%2C%20then%20the%20calendars%20of%20the%20previous%20years%20which%20followed%20the%20same%20template%20also%20need%20to%20be%20disowned.%20Would%20they%20come%20clean%20on%20the%20veracity%20of%20the%20published%20material%20in%20the%20earlier%20calendars%20and%20disown%20all%20the%20previous%20ones%2C%20too%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EC.P.%20Rajendran%20is%20an%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Advanced%20Studies%2C%20Bengaluru.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704159037000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F08162620%2Fiit.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fhow-a-calendar-exposes-the-falling-professional-standards-of-an-iit%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Relying%20on%20a%20baffling%20mixture%20of%20symbols%20and%20images%2C%20the%202024%20calendar%20claiming%20to%20be%20published%20by%20IIT-Kharagpur%20wrongly%20propagates%20that%20Vedic%20Aryans%20were%20indigenous%20to%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20region%2C%20and%20supports%20'out-of-India'%20migration%20against%20all%20evidence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fhow-a-calendar-exposes-the-falling-professional-standards-of-an-iit%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HUL%20receives%20Rs%20447.5%20cr%20GST%20demands%20and%20penalties%2C%20firm%20to%20make%20assessment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704158763000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-03%2F27%2Ffull%2F1679930913-5844.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhul-receives-rs-447-5-cr-gst-dem