l%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bangladesh%20Court%20Convicts%20Nobel%20Laureate%20Muhammad%20Yunus%20in%20Labour%20Law%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25121740%2Fcb258158-9fbe-42fb-9d0c-f1eae7617e82.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EBangladesh%20Nobel%20laureate%20economist%20Muhammad%20Yunus%20has%20been%20convicted%20by%20a%20Dhaka%20court%20on%20charges%20of%20labour%20law%20violation.%20The%20charges%20and%20his%20conviction%20are%20being%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpolitically%20motivated%E2%80%9D%20by%20his%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20allegation%20of%20violating%20the%20Labour%20Law%20against%20him%20has%20been%20proved.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20allegation%20has%20not%20been%20barred%20by%20limitation%20(either)%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20labour%20court%20judge%20Sheikh%20Merina%20Sultana%20while%20pronouncing%20the%20judgment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fworld%2Fnobel-laureate-economist-dr-muhammad-yunus-sentenced-to-6-months-in-jail-by-bangladesh-court%2Fcid%2F1990798%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20PTI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20Yunus%2C%20three%20other%20executives%20of%20Grameen%20Telecom%2C%20a%20social%20business%20company%20he%20founded%2C%20were%20awarded%20six%20months%20of%20simple%20or%20non-rigorous%20imprisonment.%20They%20were%20immediately%20granted%20one-month%20bail%20after%20furnishing%20bonds%20of%20Taka%205%2C000%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20verdict%20is%20unprecedented%2C%E2%80%9D%20Abdullah%20Al%20Mamun%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20Yunus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fnobel-peace-laureate-muhammad-yunus-convicted-in-bangladesh-labour-law-case%2Farticle67695080.ece%5C%22%3Etold%20AFP%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20did%20not%20get%20justice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convicted%20individuals%20are%20expected%20to%20appeal%20the%20verdict%20in%20the%20High%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYunus%E2%80%99s%20supporters%20see%20charges%20against%20him%20and%20the%20firms%20he%20founded%20are%20a%20result%20of%20his%20protracted%20row%20with%20Sheikh%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20government.%20Hasina%20accused%20him%20of%20%E2%80%9Csucking%20blood%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20poor.%20The%20charge%20against%20Yunus%20and%20three%20colleagues%20from%20Grameen%20Telecom%20is%20that%20the%20firm%20violated%20labour%20laws%20by%20failing%20to%20create%20a%20workers%E2%80%99%20welfare%20fund%20in%20the%20company.%20Yunus%20is%20facing%20over%20100%20other%20charges%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2083-year-old%20Nobel%20Prize%20winner%2C%20who%20won%20the%20award%20in%202006%2C%20is%20credited%20for%20lifting%20millions%20out%20of%20poverty%20through%20his%20anti-poverty%20campaign%20through%20the%20Grameen%20Bank%2C%20a%20mode%20which%20was%20replicated%20across%20continents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202008%20when%20Hasina%20assumed%20power%2C%20Yunus%E2%80%99s%20nearly%2050%20social%20business%20firms%20have%20been%20through%20several%20investigations%20for%20allegedd%20violations%20of%20several%20laws.%20In%20August%2C%20160%20global%20figures%2C%20including%20former%20US%20president%20Barack%20Obama%20and%20ex-United%20Nations%20secretary-general%20Ban%20Ki-moon%2C%20published%20a%20joint%20letter%20denouncing%20%E2%80%9Ccontinuous%20judicial%20harassment%E2%80%9D%20of%20Yunus.%20The%20letter%2C%20which%20was%20also%20signed%20by%20over%20100%20Nobel%20Prize%20winners%2C%20said%20they%20feared%20for%20%E2%80%9Chis%20safety%20and%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704112394000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25121740%2Fcb258158-9fbe-42fb-9d0c-f1eae7617e82.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbangladesh-court-convicts-nobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-in-labour-