3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20the%20first%20seven%20months%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year%202023-24%2C%20India%20experienced%20a%20trade%20deficit%20with%20nine%20of%20its%20top%20ten%20trade%20partners%2C%20with%20only%20the%20US%20showing%20a%20surplus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Findia-runs-trade-deficit-with-9%2F10-top-partners%2Farticleshow%2F106429244.cms%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trade%20surplus%20with%20the%20US%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20trading%20partner%2C%20amounted%20to%20%2419.59%20billion%2C%20while%20deficits%20with%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20the%20UAE%20reached%20%2451.11%20billion%2C%20%2433.56%20billion%2C%20and%20%246.83%20billion%2C%20respectively%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20Russia%2C%20the%20imports%20are%20of%20petrol%2C%20high%20calorific%20value%20coal%2C%20coke%20and%20briquettes%2C%20and%20fertiliser%2C%20especially%20potash.%20Our%20exports%20of%20gems%20and%20jewellery%20to%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20the%20US%20have%20declined%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20official%20told%20the%20business%20daily.%20With%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20the%20trade%20gap%20was%20%247.59%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20April-November%20period%20of%20FY24%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20merchandise%20exports%20decreased%20by%206.51%25%20to%20%24278.8%20billion%2C%20and%20imports%20fell%20by%208.67%25%20to%20%24445.15%20billion%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrade%20deficits%20were%20also%20recorded%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Singapore%2C%20and%20South%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20Indonesia%2C%20the%20trade%20deficit%20is%20because%20of%20edible%20oil.%20It%20was%20getting%20normalised%20because%20of%20rice%20and%20sugar%20exports%20to%20them%20but%20now%20those%20are%20restricted%20and%20the%20deficit%20has%20increased%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20official%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20India%20has%20traditionally%20had%20a%20deficit%20with%20Korea%20despite%20the%20two%20inking%20a%20Comprehensive%20Economic%20Partnership%20Agreement%20in%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%C2%A0Iran%20has%20reduced%20its%20tea%20and%20rice%20imports%20from%20India%20because%20of%20foreign%20exchange%20issues%20and%20finalisation%20of%20the%20rupee-payment%20mechanism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20exports%20to%20Iran%20dipped%2047%25%20year-on-year%20to%20%24567%20million%20in%20April-October%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Fisrael-hamas-conflict-hits-indias-export-prospects-to-iran%2Farticle67692771.ece%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EHindu%20BusinessLine%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20has%20severely%20damaged%20revival%20prospects%20of%20these%20exports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20business%20daily%2C%20the%20decrease%20is%20attributed%20to%20a%20minimal%20rupee%20balance%20in%20the%20rupee-rial%20account.%20India%20still%20imports%20certain%20agricultural%20products%20from%20Iran%2C%20such%20as%20saffron%2C%20which%20generates%20rupee%20balance%2C%20however%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20little%2C%20a%20source%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20oil%20imports%2C%20which%20accounted%20for%20most%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20imports%20earlier%2C%20are%20still%20suspended%2C%20the%20rupee-rial%20mechanism%20is%20almost%20non-functional%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20source%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20have%20seen%20similar%20situations%20earlier%20also%2C%20the%20global%20trade%20environment%20is%20uncertain%20because%20of%20geopolitical%20issues%20and%20a%20general%20slowdown%20across%20developed%20economies.%20Our%20exports%20and%20trade%20balance%20are%20getting%20impacted%20by%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ajay%20Sahai%2C%20director%20general%20of%20the%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Export%20Organisations%20(FIEO)%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20as%20per%20experts%2C%20reviews%20of%20existing%20free%20trade%20agreements%20are%20unlikely%20to%20address%20the%20trade%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704109883000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F19151431%2Fimage-920.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-records-trade-deficit-with-nine-top-trading-partners-in-april-october-fy24-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20total%20merchandise%20exports%20decreased%20by%206.51%25%20to%20%24278.8%20billion%2C%20and%20imports%20fell%20by%208.67%25%20to%20%24445.15%20billion%20during%20the%20same%20period.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-records-trade-deficit-with-nine-top-trading-partners-in-april-october-fy24-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Is%20Ayushmann%20Khurrana%20manifesting%20an%20Oscar%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704109544000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106454794%2Cimgsize-13050.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fis-ayushmann-khurrana-manifesting-an-oscar-in-the-coming-years-see-post-inside%2Farticleshow%2F106454794.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106454794.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAyushmann%20Khurrana%20took%20to%20his%20social%20media%20handle%20and%20gives%20a%20peek%20into%20his%202023%20and%20manifestations%20for%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2