most-important-elections-you-just-missed%2F%5C%22%3Ecan%20be%20attributed%20to%20a%20blend%20of%20well-executed%20strategies%20and%20strong%20central-state%20coordination%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20party%E2%80%99s%20projection%20of%20a%20decisive%20leader%2C%20coupled%20with%20welfare%20policies%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20model%2C%20proved%20effective.%20Moreover%2C%20their%20secular%20and%20inclusive%20stance%2C%20alongside%20leveraging%20anti-incumbency%20sentiments%2C%20significantly%20contributed%20to%20their%20triumph.%20The%20victory%20was%20further%20bolstered%20by%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20whose%20subtle%20yet%20impactful%20support%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role.%20These%20combined%20factors%20were%20instrumental%20in%20shaping%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20and%20subsequent%20electoral%20success%20in%20Telangana.%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20success%20validated%20the%20Karnataka%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeadership%3A%20The%20rise%20of%20Anumula%20Revanth%C2%A0Reddy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA.R.%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20ascent%20as%20a%20leader%20in%20Telangana%20offers%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20leadership%20crises%20and%20internal%20conflicts%20plaguing%20the%20Congress%20in%20other%20states%20like%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Rajasthan.%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20positioning%20was%20vital%20both%20for%20dealing%20with%20factions%20and%20the%20ideological%20narrative.%20Reddy%20was%20strategically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ftelangana%2Frevanth-reddy-former-telangana-tdp-leader-joins-congress%2Farticle19956467.ece%5C%22%3Epicked%20from%20the%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20in%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20state%20where%20the%20Congress%20party%20had%20been%20politically%20wiped%20out.%20The%20central%20leadership%20had%20counterintuitively%20chosen%20a%20dark%20horse%20from%20an%20opposition%20party%2C%20to%20perform%20an%20impossible%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevanth%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20political%20acumen%2C%20evidenced%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatvnews.com%2Felections%2Ftelangana-assembly-elections-telangana-assembly-elections-key-candidates-kcr-owaisi-uttam-kumar-reddy-jana-reddy-revanth-reddy-l-ramana-489261%5C%22%3Ehis%20victory%20in%20the%202009%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20assembly%20elections%20as%20a%20TDP%20candidate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20marked%20him%20as%20a%20potentially%20promising%20regional%20figure.%20The%20TDP%20leader%20had%20snatched%20the%20Kodangal%20seat%20from%20a%20five-time%20incumbent%20Congress%20MLA%20many%20years%20before%20the%20birth%20of%20Telangana.%20The%20political%20landscape%E2%80%99s%20shift%20following%20Y.S.%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20demise%20and%20the%20bifurcation%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20in%202013%20presented%20new%20challenges.%20While%20the%20TDP%20struggled%20in%20Telangana%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Telangana%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(TRS)%20further%20complicated%20the%20scenario.%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20resilience%20shone%20as%20he%20continued%20to%20assert%20his%20political%20relevance%2C%20winning%20the%202014%20Telangana%20assembly%20elections%20as%20a%20TDP%20candidate.%20His%20strategic%20alignment%20with%20the%20Congress%20party%20in%202017%2C%20despite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fmajor-upset-cong-revanth-reddy-loses-kodangal-trs-patnam-narender-93202%5C%22%3Ean%20initial%20defeat%20in%20the%202018%20state%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20a%20calculated%20move%20of%20the%20Congress%20leadership.%20The%20party%20could%20successfully%20offer%20a%20promising%20possibility%20to%20a%20leader.%20Rejuvenating%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20influence%20in%20Telangana%20needed%20a%20dark%20horse%20like%20Reddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22As%20Modi%20Decrees%20a%20New%20Diwali%2C%20Remember%20There's%20More%20to%20Indian%20Politics%20Than%20BJP's%20Ram%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-modi-decrees-a-new-diwali-remember-theres-more-to-indian-politics-than-bjps-ram%5C%22%3EAs%20Modi%20Decrees%20a%20New%20Diwali%2C%20Remember%20There%E2%80%99s%20More%20to%20Indian%20Politics%20Than%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Ram%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20leadership%20style%2C%20marked%20by%20dedication%20to%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20causes%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Frevanth_anumula%2Fstatus%2F1732035504810627240%3Fs%3D61%26t%3Dt8H-NDw_yS0-vBT8F1Jgsw%5C%22%3Eloyalty%20to%20the%20Gandhi%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20highlights%20his%20capability%20to%20balance%20local%20and%20national%20political%20dynamics.%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20evolution%20from%20a%20regional%20to%20a%20national%20figure%20exemplifies%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20deft%20and%20pragmatic%20handling%20of%20regional%20leadership%2C%20which%20needs%20emulation%20in%20other%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWelfare%20policies%3A%20Echoing%20the%20Karnataka%20model%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Telangana%20campaign%20followed%20the%20Karnataka%20welfare%20model%20to%20the%20T.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-polls-how-obcs-figured-in-the-electoral-discourse-of-political-parties%5C%22%3EThe%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%E2%80%99s%20(BRS)%20approach%20was%20clientelistic.%3C%2Fa%3E%20It%20focused%20on%20targeted%20redistributions%20favouring%20certain%20groups.%20The%20BRS%E2%80%99s%20initiatives%20like%20the%20Kula%20Vruthi%20OBC%20Development%20Fund%20and%20the%20Rythu%20Bandhu%20scheme%20were%20criticised%20for%20perpetuating%20caste%20and%20occupation-based%20divisions%20rather%20than%20promoting%20broad%20empowerment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20stark%20contrast%2C%20the%20Congress%20in%20Telangana%20adopted%20a%20dual%20approach%2C%20combining%20clientelism%20with%20programmatic%20welfare%20measures.%20These%20programmatic%20policies%20were%20designed%20with%20clear%2C%20non-discriminatory%20eligibility%20rules%2C%20aiming%20to%20benefit%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20societal%20groups.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Felections%2Ftelangana-assembly-polls-2023%2Fstory%2Flpg-cylinder-for-rs-500-free-bus-travel-6-guarantees-by-congress-in-telangana-2436939-2023-09-17%5C%22%3EThe%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20promises%20included%20diverse%20schemes%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98Mahalakshmi%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Rythu%20Bharosa%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Gruha%20Jyothi%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Indiramma%20Indlu%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Yuva%20Vikasam%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98Cheyutha%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fa%3E%20These%20initiatives%2C%20including%20free%20electricity%20units%2C%20subsidised%20LPG%20cylinders%2C%20land%20distribution%2C%20and%20educational%20support%2C%20were%20intended%20to%20appeal%20to%20various%20demographics%2C%20including%20women%2C%20farmers%2C%20students%2C%20and%20disadvantaged%20groups.%20The%20most%20important%20feature%20was%20the%20considerable%20investment%20in%20all%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20balanced%20approach%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20integrating%20targeted%20benefits%20for%20specific%20groups%20with%20broad-based%20inclusive%20schemes%2C%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20their%20electoral%20triumph.%20It%20allowed%20the%20party%20to%20address%20the%20unique%20needs%20of%20different%20groups%20while%20projecting%20an%20image%20of%20inclusive%20development%2C%20capturing%20the%20support%20of%20a%20larger%20section%20of%20the%20electorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecularism%20and%20inclusivity%3A%20Beyond%20soft%20Hindutva%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20steadfast%20adherence%20to%20secularism%20and%20inclusivity%20significantly%20influenced%20their%20victory%20in%20the%20Telangana%20elections%2C%20distinguishing%20their%20approach%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-narrative-polls-bjp-hindutva%5C%22%3Esoft%20Hindutva%20stance%3C%2Fa%3E%20observed%20in%20states%20like%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20Karnataka%20was%20the%20only%20state%20that%20followed%20the%20Karnataka%20model%20in%20the%20November%202023%20elections.%20%C2%A0This%20strategy%20resonated%20with%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20diverse%20populace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20to%20this%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Felections%2Ftelangana%2Felections-trelangana-cong-declaration-2765346%5C%22%3EMinority%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20bold%20initiative%20pledging%20substantial%20budget%20increases%20for%20minority%20welfare%2C%20up%20to%20Rs%204%2C000%20crore%20annually.%20This%20commitment%20aimed%20at%20uplifting%20minority%20communities%20through%20enhanced%20support%20and%20representation.%20The%20party%20also%20promised%20a%20caste%20census%20to%20ensure%20equitable%20distribution%20of%20resources%20and%20opportunities%20among%20all%20backward%20classes%2C%20including%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Odisha%20Congress%20Leaders%20Hopeful%20of%20Revival%2C%20but%20Is%20It%20Realistic%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fodish-congress-hope-revival-bjd-bjp%5C%22%3EOdisha%20Congress%20Leaders%20Hopeful%20of%20Revival%2C%20but%20Is%20It%20Realistic%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20Congress%20proposed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ftelangana-polls-congress-releases-minority-declaration-promises-rs-4000-cr-budget-for-welfare%2Farticleshow%2F105110475.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eallocating%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore%20annually%20for%20subsidised%20loans%20to%20unemployed%20minority%20youth%20and%20women%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20augmenting%20their%20economic%20empowerment.%20The%20Abdul%20Kalam%20Taufa-e-Taleem%20Scheme%20was%20another%20significant%20measure%2C%20offering%20financial%20assistance%20up%20to%20Rs%205%20lakh%20to%20minority%20youths%20pursuing%20higher%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20also%20visibly%20embraced%20diversity.%20Leaders%20actively%20visited%20religious%20sites%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmunsifdaily.com%2Fa-day-before-polling-in-telangana-revanth-reddy-offers-prayers-at-temple-dargahvideo%2F%5C%22%3Evarious%20communities%2C%20including%20mosques%2C%20temples%2C%20and%20other%20holy%20places%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20promoting%20solidarity%20and%20respect%20across%20faiths.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20Dalit%20leaders%20in%20these%20visits%20symbolised%20a%20unified%20stance%20against%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comprehensive%20approach%2C%20combining%20welfare%20initiatives%20with%20visible%20inclusivity%20in%20religious%20engagements%2C%20broadened%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20appeal.%20It%20attracted%20not%20only%20minority%20communities%20but%20also%20voters%20favouring%20a%20secular%20and%20inclusive%20political%20framework%2C%20thereby%20fortifying%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20position%20and%20contributing%20to%20its%20electoral%20success%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECivic%20synergy%3A%20NGO%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Es%20and%20the%20Congress%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelangana%20had%20its%20own%20version%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CEddelu%20Karnataka%E2%80%9D%20(Wake%20up%20Karnataka)%20movement.%20In%20Telangana%2C%20a%20consortium%20of%20local%20civil%20society%20organisations%20played%20a%20pivotal%2C%20albeit%20subtle%2C%20role%20in%20shaping%20the%20political%20landscape.%20Groups%20such%20as%20Telangana%20People%E2%80%99s%20Joint%20Action%20Committee%20(JAC)%2C%20Jago%20Telangana%2C%20Bharat%20Bachao%2C%20Telangana%20Samakhya%20and%20Muslim%20Organisations%20JAC%20formed%20a%20robust%20network%2C%20echoing%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20various%20social%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20groups%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Ftelangana-assembly%2Fcivil-society-organisations-back-the-move-for-change-in-telangana%2Farticle67570043.ece%5C%22%3EBharat%20Jodo%20Abhiyaan%2C%20led%20by%20national%20convener%20Yogendra%20Yadav%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20a%20democratic%20India%2C%20where%20the%20Constitution%20and%20equality%20of%20all%20communities%20are%20upheld.%20Their%20stance%20was%20clear%3A%20to%20defeat%20the%20BJP%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20the%20upcoming%20elections%2C%20both%20at%20the%20state%20and%20national%20levels.%20This%20movement%20saw%20the%20participation%20of%20hundreds%20of%20senior%20social%20activists%20and%20leaders%2C%20reflecting%20a%20widespread%20desire%20for%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20organisations%2C%20steered%20by%20influential%20civil%20society%20figures%2C%20became%20a%20collective%20voice%20for%20political%20change%2C%20working%20in%20tandem%20but%20not%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20the%20Congress%20campaign.%20Their%20activities%20spanned%20organising%20events%2C%20mobilising%20public%20opinion%2C%20and%20active%20campaigning%20across%20Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20the%20Congress%20learn%20the%20lesson%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Telangana%20victory%20is%20the%20result%20of%20a%20well-executed%20strategy%20encompassing%20strong%20leadership%2C%20welfare-oriented%20policies%2C%20secularism%20and%20civil%20society%20support%2C%20all%20within%20the%20challenging%20environment%20of%20competitive%20authoritarianism.%20The%20Congress%20faces%20a%20critical%20choice%20between%20the%20successful%20Karnataka%20model%20that%20worked%20in%20Telangana%2C%20which%20is%20very%20different%20from%20the%20factional%20feuds%20and%20soft-Hindutva%20strategies%20that%20failed%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Rajasthan.%20The%202024%20national%20elections%20could%20mark%20the%20las