%80%99%2C%20is%20one%20such%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20China%20launched%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fchina-launches-mystery-reusable-spaceplane-for-third-time%2F%5C%22%3Ethird%20spaceplane%3C%2Fa%3E%20mission.%20Its%20first%20spaceplane%20mission%20in%20September%202020%20lasted%20only%20for%20two%20days.%20The%20second%20mission%2C%20which%20started%20from%20August%202022%20till%20May%202023%2C%20was%20operational%20for%20276%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20mission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thinkchina.sg%2Fchinas-strides-spaceflight-put-us-notice%5C%22%3Ewas%20launched%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20December%2019%2C%202023.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20known%20for%20how%20many%20days%20or%20years%20this%20mission%20will%20last.%20During%20the%20ongoing%20mission%2C%20China%20has%20deployed%20six%20%E2%80%98mysterious%20wingmen%E2%80%99%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20orbit%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-space-plane-deployed-6-mysterious-wingmen-in-orbit-claims-amateur-astronomer-4712071%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20suggest%20that%20these%20missions%20could%20be%20testing%20satellite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurasiantimes.com%2Fus-india-caught-off-guard-as-china-tests-swarm-drone-technology-that-can-outflank-enemy-defences%2F%5C%22%3Eswarm%20technology.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceplanes%20are%20not%20a%20new%20concept.%20Research%20and%20several%20debates%20have%20been%20held%20on%20this%20subject%20since%20the%20early%201960s.%20Apart%20from%20the%20US%20and%20USSR%20(now%20Russia)%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Japan%20have%20undertaken%20such%20missions%20in%20experiment%20mode%20or%20as%20fully%20operational%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20spaceplane%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20a%20combination%20of%20aircraft%20and%20spacecraft.%20It%20flies%20(or%20glides)%20like%20an%20aircraft%20within%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%20and%20operates%20as%20a%20spacecraft%20in%20outer%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20that%20the%20first%20two-day%20mission%20launched%20by%20China%20was%20more%20like%20a%20prototype%20mission%2C%20and%20the%20second%20mission%2C%20which%20lasted%20for%20around%20nine%20months%2C%20could%20have%20given%20China%20the%20necessary%20confidence%20to%20plan%20more%20such%20missions.%20During%20the%20second%20mission%2C%20the%20spaceplane%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.yahoo.com%2Fchinas-mysterious-spaceplane-raises-orbit-180000405.html%3Fguccounter%3D1%26guce_referrer%3DaHR0cHM6Ly90aGV3aXJlLmluLw%26guce_referrer_sig%3DAQAAAERzdAM2o3LsfJMiKuhuhSJZibN1l5p1j6Quxz2-V0mpSO2D6M0-orYhCEfECg0OFZEvn-J7NLioymYNxSu4414lfrzw8TvTawmFCqYJOLREPHoDQyX7gi7q19Dkrj1810RAKDCWju6LjJ9P2HsUpRYDgEP69fik1nk3ZvLUfU0U%5C%22%3Eperformed%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20orbit-raising%20maneuver%20on%20August%2025%2C%202022.%20It%20was%20in%20a%20near-circular%20597%20by%20608-kilometre%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20indicates%20that%20China%20has%20developed%20a%20capability%20to%20position%20a%20craft%20in%20different%20orbits%20in%20a%20single%20mission.%20This%20reusable%20craft%20has%20been%20developed%20by%20the%20China%20Aerospace%20Science%20and%20Technology%20Corporation%20(CASC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20three%20missions%20demonstrate%20China%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20developing%20reusable%20spaceplane%20technology%20and%20improved%20capabilities%20in%20the%20arenas%20like%20heat%20shields%20and%20landing%20equipment.%20Some%20experts%20believe%20that%20since%20this%20plane%20had%20demonstrated%20the%20capability%20of%20very%20high-speed%20re-entry%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%2C%20possibly%20this%20could%20assist%20China%E2%80%99s%20hypersonic%20missile%20program.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20mention%20that%20China%20already%20has%20a%20reasonably%20well-established%20hypersonic%20weapons%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20earlier%20mentioned%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20recent%20spaceplane%20has%20deployed%20six%20%E2%80%98mysterious%20wingmen%E2%80%99%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20orbit.%20Currently%2C%20these%20objects%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wionews.com%2Fworld%2Fus-plans-to-beat-china-in-launch-of-secret-space-plane-spacex-foils-plan-670084%5C%22%3Ebeing%20tracked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20US%20Space%20Force.%20For%20ease%20of%20tracking%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fchina-space-plane-depoyed-mystery-objects%5C%22%3Ehave%20named%3C%2Fa%3E%20them%20as%20OBJECT%20A%20through%20F.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20are%20in%20a%20similar%20orbit%20and%20are%20known%20to%20have%20moved%20closer%20to%20each%20other.%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20emitting%20different%20types%20of%20signals.%20They%20are%20expected%20to%20make%20several%20close%20approaches%20with%20each%20other%20in%20future.%20During%20earlier%20missions%2C%20too%2C%20Chinese%20spaceplanes%20had%20released%20some%20objects%20in%20space%2C%20which%20were%20also%20tracked%20by%20the%20US%20Space%20Force.%20Experts%20believe%20that%20this%20time%2C%20the%20six%20objects%20show%20a%20different%20radio%20behaviour%20in%20comparison%20with%20the%20objects%20released%20during%20the%20earlier%20two%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPossibly%2C%20the%20technology%20used%20by%20China%20to%20design%20and%20develop%20these%20spaceplanes%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popularmechanics.com%2Fmilitary%2Fa46190887%2Fx-37b-vs-shenlong-spaceplane%2F%5C%22%3EBoeing%20X-37B%3C%2Fa%3E%20(the%20secretive%20US%20spaceplane).%20This%20craft%20is%20a%20robotic%20autonomous%20vehicle%20and%20has%20been%20in%20NASA%E2%80%99s%20service%20since%202010.%20NASA%20and%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20have%20already%20undertaken%20six%20launches%20of%20this%20vehicle.%20The%20US%20has%20developed%20two%20vehicles%20in%20this%20category%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20their%20missions%20stayed%20in%20space%20for%20a%20period%20of%20around%20two%20years.%20The%20last%20mission%2C%20which%20got%20back%20to%20Earth%20during%20November%202022%2C%20was%20out%20there%20for%20908%20days.%20These%20missions%20were%20at%20an%20orbit%20of%20around%20400%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20US%20administration%20has%20been%20totally%20silent%20about%20the%20rationale%20behind%20undertaking%20these%20missions.%20Possibly%2C%20they%20could%20have%20conducted%20on-orbit%20science%20and%20military-related%20experiments%20during%20the%20long%20stay%20of%20these%20crafts%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20obvious%20that%20both%20the%20US%20and%20the%20Chinese%20agencies%20must%20have%20gathered%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20atmospheric%2C%20space%20weather-related%20and%20reconnaissance%20data%20(continuous%20data%20sets).%20Such%20data%20could%20be%20utilised%20for%20the%20development%20of%20various%20mathematical%20models.%20It%20is%20known%20that%20the%20worth%20of%20various%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20algorithms%20depends%20much%20on%20data%20inputs%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20such%20humongous%20data%20could%20help%20these%20nations%20in%20fine-tuning%20their%20AI-based%20scientific%20and%20military%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20conducting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.dtic.mil%2Fsti%2Fcitations%2FADA468025%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520January%252011%252C%25202007%252C%2520the%2Cconcerns%2520about%2520more%2520space%2520debris.%5C%22%3Eanti-satellite%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ASAT)%20during%202007%2C%20China%20is%20found%20to%20have%20systematically%20developed%20its%20counter-space%20program.%20The%20messaging%20behind%20this%20test%20was%20very%20clear%3A%20China%20would%20not%20hesitate%20to%20take%20the%20warfare%20to%20outer%20space.%20After%20this%20test%2C%20concerns%20were%20raised%20over%20China%E2%80%99s%20reckless%20creation%20of%20space%20debris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202023%20witnessed%20China%20undertaking%20various%20important%20space%20missions.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20invested%20in%20some%20basic%20technologies%20which%20have%20been%20in%20use%20for%20centuries%2C%20such%20as%20high-altitude%20balloon%20missions.%20In%20early%202023%2C%20a%20Chinese%20balloon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchinese-spy-balloon-spotted-over-us-says-pentagon%5C%22%3Ehad%20intruded%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20airspace%2C%20and%20in%20December%2C%20a%20balloon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Ftaiwan-detected-two-chinese-balloons-crossing-taiwan-strait-sunday-defence-2023-12-18%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20detected%3C%2Fa%3E%20moving%20across%20the%20Taiwan%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20spaceplanes%20to%20balloons%2C%20China%20has%20been%20using%20a%20range%20of%20technologies%20for%20reconnaissance%2C%20undertaking%20experimentation%20(possibly%20of%20military%20relevance)%20and%20data%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20some%20decades%20ago%2C%20debates%20were%20going%20on%20in%20the%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO)%20circles%20over%20the%20development%20of%20a%20spaceplane%20and%20a%20project%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdefenceforumindia.com%2Fthreads%2Fhypersonic-vehicles-scramjets.155%2F%5C%22%3Ecalled%3C%2Fa%3E%20AVATAR%20(Aerobic%20Vehicle%20for%20Hypersonic%20Aerospace%20Transportation).%20Possibly%2C%20the%20idea%20was%20to%20develop%20a%20system%20for%20undertaking%20low-cost%20military%20and%20commercial%20satellite%20launches.%20Satellite%20swarm%20technologies%20have%20great%20scientific%20and%20strategic%20potential%20and%20now%20the%20time%20has%20come%20for%20India%20to%20take%20the%20projects%20like%20AVATAR%20to%20its%20logical%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjey%20Lele%20researches%20space%20issues%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EInstitutions%20That%20Shaped%20Modern%20India%3A%20ISRO%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704092418000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01120225%2Fimage-1680.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fa-look-at-chinas-ambitious-spaceplane-missions%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20December%2C%20China%20launched%20its%20third%20spaceplane%20mission%2C%20deploying%20six%20'mysterious%20wingmen'%20into%20the%20Earth's%20orbit.%20Currently%2C%20these%20objects%20are%20being%20tracked%20by%20the%20US%20Space%20Force.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fa-look-at-chinas-ambitious-spaceplane-missions%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%202024%2C%20India%20Will%20Bank%20on%20Political%20Satirists%20%E2%80%93%20Its%20Remaining%20Truth-Tellers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01115418%2FIMG_2856-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%202024%2C%20and%20we%20have%20learnt%20that%20in%20a%20month%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fgovernment%2F141-here-are-all-the-mps-suspended-from-parliament-this-winter-session%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3E146%20legislators%20are%20suspended%20from%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20biggest%20news%20can%20still%20surround%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fmimicry-jagdeep-dhankhar-kalyan-banerjee%5C%22%3Ethe%20tragic%20art%20of%20mimicry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Little%20blurs%20the%20lines%20between%20the%20joke%2C%20the%20jester%2C%20serious%20political%20events%20unfolding%20and%20the%20business%20of%20narrating%20them.%20But%20who%20gets%20to%20tell%20the%20joke%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20September%2029%2C%20the%20comedian%20Varun%20Grover%20said%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%2C%20the%20most%20dangerous%20job%20is%20that%20of%20a%20comedian%E2%80%99s.%E2%80%9D%20Four%20days%20later%2C%20his%20longtime%20collaborator%2C%20the%20comedian%20Sanjay%20Rajoura%2C%20was%20among%20100%20people%20raided%20and%20questioned%20by%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20special%20branch%20over%20connections%20with%20the%20news%20site%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENewsClick%20is%20accused%20of%20having%20terror%20connections%20%E2%80%93%20largely%20bolstered%20by%20an%20unsubstantiated%20line%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20piece%20over%20its%20financial%20backer%E2%80%99s%20China%20ties.%20Its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdelhi-police-conducts-early-morning-raids-at-houses-of-journalists-satirists%5C%22%3Efounder%20and%20an%20HR%20head%20have%20been%20in%20jail%20since%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20NewsClick%20released%20a%20statement%20on%20how%20its%20employees%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fnewsclick-it-department-accounts-frozen%5C%22%3Esalaries%20were%20held%20by%20central%20agencies%E2%80%99%20freezing%20action%20on%20its%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Many%20of%20these%20employees%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1057022%2Fno-one-spared-in-newsclick-raids-young-staffers-part-time-employees-freelance-contributors%5C%22%3Ealready%20had%20their%20devices%20seized%20by%20police%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20October%20raids.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20as%20close%20to%20brow-beating%20an%20enterprise%20to%20fold%20up%20as%20it%20gets.%20Perhaps%20Grover%20is%20wrong.%20Perhaps%20the%20most%20dangerous%20job%20is%20that%20of%20a%20journalist%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20lone%20comedian%20who%20has%20thrown%20in%20their%20lot%20with%20journalists.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20some%20significance%2C%20therefore%2C%20that%20there%20are%20so%20many%20of%20those%20lone%20comedians%20who%20have%20thrown%20in%20their%20lot%20with%20journalists%2C%20today.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20YouTube%2C%20on%20X%2C%20on%20Instagram%20and%20that%20ancient%20gossip%20haunt%2C%20Facebook%2C%20political%20satirists%20have%20been%20launching%20no-holds-barred%20spiels%20on%20the%20nitty%20gritties%20of%20polarising%20politics%2C%20unwieldy%20policies%20and%20the%20intolerant%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmedia-organisations-write-chandrachud-freedom-press%5C%22%3E161st%20out%20of%20180%20countries%20on%20the%20world%20press%20freedom%20index%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20news%20organisations%20are%20labouring%20under%20changing%20digital%20landscapes%2C%20malicious%20defamation%20suits%20and%20prohibitive%20laws%20that%20make%20functioning%20a%20pain%2C%20you%20feel%20as%20if%20a%20handful%20of%20the%20online%20satirists%20of%20the%20day%20have%20taken%20over%20the%20onus%20of%20speaking%20truth%20to%20power%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20it%20comes%20with%20a%20dose%20of%20snideness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20many%20of%20them%2C%20it%20does%20not%20take%20much%20to%20launch%20into%20satire.%20It%20is%20not%20that%20our%20moment%20is%20so%20grotesque%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20satirise.%20It%20is%20that%20our%20moment%20is%20so%20grotesque%2C%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20satirise.%20Does%20this%20fact%20weigh%20on%20the%20tellers%20to%20the%20point%20of%20hopelessness%3F%20Can%20news%20really%20be%20entertainment%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSatire%20has%20become%20like%20regular%20news%20for%20people.%20People%20would%20rather%20listen%20to%20jokes%20around%20the%20news.%20i